{"title": "Nibelungenlied", "description": "Das Nibelungenlied ist ein mittelalterliches Heldenepos und wurde oft als \u201eNationalepos der Deutschen\u201c bezeichnet. Es entstand zu Beginn des 13. Jahrhunderts und wurde in der damaligen Volkssprache Mittelhochdeutsch geschrieben.<br>\nDas Epos erz\u00e4hlt von der Liebe zwischen dem Drachent\u00f6ter Siegfried und der burgundischen Prinzessin Kriemhild, von der Brautwerbung des burgundischen K\u00f6nigs Gunther um die isl\u00e4ndische K\u00f6nigin Brunhild, vom Verrat der Burgunden an Siegfried und dessen Ermordung durch Hagen. Sp\u00e4ter ist der Schauplatz der Handlung das Land der Hunnen unter K\u00f6nig Etzel, den Kriemhild in zweiter Ehe geheiratet hat. Kriemhild benutzt ihre neue Position, um mithilfe der Hunnen Siegfrieds Tod an Hagen und allen Burgunden zu r\u00e4chen.<br>\nDie \u00dcbersetzung Karl Joseph Simrocks geh\u00f6rt zu den bekanntesten \u00dcbertragungen des alten Textes in die neuhochdeutsche Sprache.\n<br></br>\nThe Nibelungenlied (Song of the Nibelungs) is a medieval epic poem and has been often referred to as the German \u201cnational epic\u201d. It was written down in the early 13th century in Middle High German, the vernacular of the time.<br>\nThe epic tells of the love between the dragon-slayer Siegfried and the Burgundian princess Kriemhild, how Gunther, King of Burgundy, courts Brunhild of Iceland, and how Siegfried is betrayed by the Burgundians and murdered by Hagen. The scene of the story later shifts to the land of the Huns of King Etzel, Kriemhild\u2019s husband in second marriage. Kriemhild uses her new position among the Huns to avenge Siegfried\u2019s death on Hagen and all the Burgundians.<br>\nThe translation of Karl Joseph Simrock is one of the best-known New German versions of the old text. (Summary by Al-Kadi)", "duration": 44221, "language": "German", "authors": [{"id": "221", "name": " Unknown"}], "coverArt": "http://www.archive.org/download/librivox_cd_covers/nibelungenlied.jpg", "copyright_year": "1827", "genres": ["Action & Adventure Fiction", "Myths", "Legends & Fairy Tales", "Sagas"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Christian Al-Kadi"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Christian Al-Kadi"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Hokuspokus"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Elli"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Erstes Abenteuer", "readers": [3503], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/nibelungenlied_ak_librivox/nibelungenlied_01_simrock_64kb.mp3", "duration": 393}, {"section": 2, "title": "Zweites Abenteuer", "readers": [3503], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/nibelungenlied_ak_librivox/nibelungenlied_02_simrock_64kb.mp3", "duration": 504}, {"section": 3, "title": "Drittes Abenteuer", "readers": [3503], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/nibelungenlied_ak_librivox/nibelungenlied_03_simrock_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1649}, {"section": 4, "title": "Viertes Abenteuer", "readers": [3503], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/nibelungenlied_ak_librivox/nibelungenlied_04_simrock_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2145}, {"section": 5, "title": "F\u00fcnftes Abenteuer", "readers": [3503], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/nibelungenlied_ak_librivox/nibelungenlied_05_simrock_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1068}, {"section": 6, "title": "Sechstes Abenteuer", "readers": [3503], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/nibelungenlied_ak_librivox/nibelungenlied_06_simrock_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1193}, {"section": 7, "title": "Siebentes Abenteuer", "readers": [3503], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/nibelungenlied_ak_librivox/nibelungenlied_07_simrock_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1600}, {"section": 8, "title": "Achtes Abenteuer", "readers": [3503], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/nibelungenlied_ak_librivox/nibelungenlied_08_simrock_64kb.mp3", "duration": 865}, {"section": 9, "title": "Neuntes Abenteuer", "readers": [3503], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/nibelungenlied_ak_librivox/nibel